    "body": "I don't see any issues that are precisely this, so hopefully I'm neither missing one nor misunderstanding the expected behavior here.\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`: \r\n\r\n```\r\nNVIM v0.5.0-dev+e0a01bdf7\r\nBuild type: Release\r\nLuaJIT 2.1.0-beta3\r\nCompilation: clang -U_FORTIFY_SOURCE -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=1 -DNDEBUG -Wall -Wextra -pedantic -Wno-unused-parameter -Wstrict-prototypes -std=gnu99 -Wshadow -Wconversion -Wmissing-prototypes -Wimplicit-fallthrough -Wvla -fstack-protector-strong -fno-common -fdiagnostics-color=auto -DINCLUDE_GENERATED_DECLARATIONS -D_GNU_SOURCE -DNVIM_MSGPACK_HAS_FLOAT32 -DNVIM_UNIBI_HAS_VAR_FROM -DMIN_LOG_LEVEL=3 -I/tmp/neovim-20210516-8989-1w35zy5/build/config -I/tmp/neovim-20210516-8989-1w35zy5/src -I/opt/homebrew/include -I/Library/Developer/CommandLineTools/SDKs/MacOSX.sdk/usr/include -I/opt/homebrew/opt/gettext/include -I/tmp/neovim-20210516-8989-1w35zy5/build/src/nvim/auto -I/tmp/neovim-20210516-8989-1w35zy5/build/include\r\nCompiled by julian@Airm.lan\r\n\r\nFeatures: +acl +iconv +tui\r\nSee \":help feature-compile\"\r\n\r\n   system vimrc file: \"$VIM/sysinit.vim\"\r\n  fall-back for $VIM: \"/opt/homebrew/Cellar/neovim/HEAD-e0a01bd_2/share/nvim\"\r\n\r\nRun :checkhealth for more info\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Operating system/version: macOS Big Sur\r\n- Terminal name/version: Kitty\r\n- `$TERM`: screen-256color\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nIf this report is about different behaviour between Nvim and Vim, make sure to\r\nread `:h vim-differences` first. Otherwise remove the next line.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\nPut the following in a file called `foo.lua`:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal bufnr = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\nlocal current = vim.api.nvim_get_current_win()\r\nvim.cmd(\"vsplit\")\r\nvim.cmd(string.format(\"buffer %d\", bufnr))\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(bufnr, 0, -1, true, vim.split(string.rep(\"foo\\n\", 100), '\\n'))\r\nvim.cmd(\"normal GG\")\r\nvim.api.nvim_set_current_win(current)\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(bufnr, 0, -1, true, vim.split(string.rep(\"bar\\n\", 10), '\\n'))\r\n-- vim.api.nvim_buf_call(bufnr, vim.fn.winline)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen run `:luafile foo.lua` from `nvim -u NORC`.\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nObserve that the second window appears blank, even though it contains lines.\r\n\r\nIf you switch into it (with `^Wh` say), the lines will appear.\r\n\r\nConfusingly, uncommenting out the line doing `winline` also will make the lines properly appear.\r\n\r\nSo will increasing the length of the replacement text so that it's as long as the original contents.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nAll examples should redraw the window (and immediately show the contents).",
